LunCoSim — third-party attribution
==================================

LunCoSim itself is licensed under Apache-2.0 (see LICENSE). This file records
attribution required by the licences of third-party font software that ships
inside, or is fetched at build time by, LunCoSim binaries and web bundles.

Rust crate dependencies carry their own licences; this NOTICE covers fonts
only, because font licences (OFL-1.1, UFL-1.0, Bitstream Vera) require the
notice to travel with the distributed binary.


DejaVu Sans (DejaVuSans.ttf), version 2.37
------------------------------------------
Used as the proportional fallback face so math, Greek and arrow glyphs render
without tofu (crates/lunco-theme/src/fonts.rs).

Not vendored in this repository. It is downloaded from the upstream release
tarball declared in crates/lunco-theme/Assets.toml and copied into
dist/<bin>/fonts/ by scripts/build_web.sh.

Licence: the DejaVu Fonts License — the DejaVu glyphs derived from Bitstream
Vera remain under the Bitstream Vera Fonts Copyright, and the DejaVu changes
were released into the public domain. The full licence text ships as LICENSE
inside the upstream dejavu-fonts-ttf-2.37 archive and is not vendored here;
confirm against that archive before redistributing.


Fonts embedded by dependencies
------------------------------
These are compiled into LunCoSim binaries via `include_bytes!` in upstream
crates, so they are redistributed by us. Licence text lives with each crate's
source in the Cargo registry at the paths noted.

Fira Mono (FiraMono-subset.ttf)
  Bevy's default font, embedded by bevy_text (src/lib.rs, DEFAULT_FONT_DATA).
  Licence: NEEDS CONFIRMATION — bevy_text ships no licence file alongside the
  TTF. Fira Mono is published under OFL-1.1 upstream; verify against the Bevy
  distribution before relying on this.

The four fonts below are embedded by epaint_default_fonts (egui), which does
vendor their licence texts in its `fonts/` directory:

Ubuntu Light (Ubuntu-Light.ttf)
  Licence: Ubuntu Font Licence 1.0 (UFL.txt).

Noto Emoji Regular (NotoEmoji-Regular.ttf)
  Licence: SIL Open Font License 1.1 (OFL.txt). The vendored OFL.txt carries
  the generic licence body with no copyright-holder line.

Hack Regular (Hack-Regular.ttf)
  Licence: MIT. Copyright 2018 Source Foundry Authors (Hack-Regular.txt).
  Its Bitstream Vera / DejaVu derived work is noted there as public domain.

emoji-icon-font (emoji-icon-font.ttf)
